bout it.<br><br>&quot;See, I never thought this day would come.  After Paramedicus left, I thought I would never find someone to love me.  But I have found that someone.&quot;<br><br>Jaranna glances around nervously, meeting the eyes of Effiliandra, who smiles at her, nodding her to go on.  Jaranna takes a deep breath and continues.  &quot;I have been in love for a long while now, but, due to things being the way they were, I could never say anything.  But things have changed, and I can now proudly say that I soon will take the surname of the love of my life.&quot;<br><br>Jaranna couldn't help but smile.  The Sisters and Brothers were seeming to talk amongst themselves, trying to figure out who it was that had stolen their Sister's heart.  Jaranna looked down at her still-shaking hand, and the smile faded.  She held up her hand for all to see.<br><br>&quot;My hand shivers.  I am so nervous I am on the verge of collapse, and that is because many of you will not like what I am about to say.&quot;  Jaranna swallows, then shakes her head.  &quot;I have said it before, and I will say it again.  I will not leave this Circle until the day I die or I am no longer wanted.  But I am deathly afraid that the latter may come to pass this day.<br><br>&quot;Many of you do not like this person, and, for some of you, that dislike is outright hatred.&quot;  Jaranna looks to Llylewen, then Arania, then back at Effie, who motions to her to go on.<br><br>&quot;We have not set a date yet, nor have we hammered out any specifics, but soon I will take a last name.<br><br>&quot;From that moment on, I will be Jaranna Lileath.&quot;<br><br>Jaranna pulled her arms up as if to hug herself, waiting to see what her family's reaction would be. <p><P>Jaranna<BR>Circle of Sisters</P><P><EM>Raven hair and ruby lips<BR>Sparks fly from her finger tips<BR>Echoed voices in the night<BR>She's a restless spirit on an endless flight</EM></P></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=20371A><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/uxstealmeapeachx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>xstealmeapeachx</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 77<br> <font color=#660000>(8/28/02 12:30:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fcircleofsistersfrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=267.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: An announcement</span><hr size=1> Kelthalas sat, calmly listening to Jaranna's speech, taking a sip of fine elven brandy from time to time. Unfortunately for those sitting around him, he was currently in the process of doing just that at the conclusion his Sister's speech. Somehow, he managed to both choke and perform a tremendous spit take simultaneously.<br>&quot;You WHAT!?!?&quot; he spluttered, his emerald green eyes looking as if they were about to pop out of their sockets.<br>Almost as suddenly as he had reacted, the ranger's features subsided. Though he appeared outwardly calm, his eyes betrayed him, the fires of anger clearly visible in their depths.<br>&quot;I would congratulate you, Jaranna, but I fear that no good will come of this.&quot; he more whispered than said.<br>&quot;Though,&quot; he mused, &quot;I suppose that your chosen will have a lifetime to change my mind.&quot;<br>Kelthalas took a final sip from his flask of brandy, his hand visibly shaking, before closing it and standing.<br>&quot;Enjoy your harem,&quot; he spat, no longer able to contain his emotions, &quot;for if you think that you are anything more than another plaything to her, I fear you are sorely mistaken.&quot;<br>Kelthalas stomped out of the hall, nearly unhinging the door again in the process.<br><br>-Kelthalas Gwendyll<br> Master of Initiates: Clan of Brothers<br> 39 Ranger of Tunare<br> Master Fletcher (189)<br> Master Baker (140)<br><br><br>(OOC: standard disclaimers apply. 