pan><hr size=1> Arania gets up from her chair and walks over to Wardenn.  Giving him a gentle hug, she reassured him things will be fine.  "Dont worry Wardenn.  Vivienne wont eat you.  i'll be sure of that."<br><br>Arania looks up to Jaranna.  "Yes, i knew of your relationship for quite some time Jaranna.  I do know that Dawninglight is no longer with Vivienne.  However, i think there is a lot you dont know about her.  I think if you did, you'd rethink your decision...  however, its your choice."  <br><br>Not looking happy, she speaks sarcasticly.  "So which lover will you be?  I hope you are very willing to share because she wont have it any other way."<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=20371A><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ujaxy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jaxy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Founding Chieftess</span><br>  Posts: 322<br> <font color=#660000>(8/28/02 9:07:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fcircleofsistersfrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=267.topic&index=11>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.eqguild.net/guilds/Eviah/azure.jpg height=100 width=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: An announcement</span><hr size=1> Eviah has been sitting in her favorite chair in the corner near the big stone hearth reading yet another book.  She likes to sit in the corner, in pretense to reading and studying, she is very aware of conversations that are voiced throughout the room, as well as who comes and goes.<br><br>She had been listening to the announcement and the aftermath.  She does not know what to say, and due to the crowd of sisters and brothers slowly forming around Jaranna, she feels she would only get in the way.<br><br>Someone opened the door and walked out, Eviah tried to see who it was, but could not in the position she was in.  A wind blew in the hall and circled through the room.  A few brown leaves strolled in riding the currents.<br><br>As the breeze touched her skin, she felt a chill creep up her spine.  There was something riding the wind today, something that wasn't right.  She frowned and looked out the window.  She tilted her head and beyond the chatter and the laughter, the loud talking and the whispers, she heard an unnatural laughter.  It was brief, and her brows furrowed together.<br><br>She glanced over at Jaranna and she silently wished her good luck and for the blessings of Tunare in love, in any form, yet something was forboding about the wind today.<br><br><br>Eviah Neige <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=20371A><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bcircleofsisters.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dalnin>Dalnin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elder<br>Paddle Mistress</span><br>  Posts: 504<br> <font color=#660000>(8/28/02 9:54:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fcircleofsistersfrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=267.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   *smile*</span><hr size=1> In the back of the room haunting as always stands the traveller. listening and not speakin, quickly slipping from your notice.<br><br>As the crowd departs, she slips up .<br><br>*with a formal curtsie*<br>&quot;Sister, I wish you well. I hope that you find happiness within the arms, and danceing on the tongue of this one.&quot;<br><br>*she pauses, as if thinking *<br>&quot; I hope you both find happieness, and I hope you're not added to the list of the cast off. &quot;<br><br>*Jaranna looks up suprised to see tears in th eyes of one that normally isn't emotional*<br><br>*Dalnin embraces Jaranna*<br>&quot;My heart goes with you sister.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=20371A><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ujelineth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jelineth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#660000>(8/28/02 10:45:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fcircleofsistersfrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=267.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: *smile*</span><hr size=1> I sit upon my chair that has been especially desginated for me. As I listen upon the sounds going on inside the guildhall, I cant help but wonder if some people are being more hypocritical then others about the Tier'dal. I have had a lovely conversation myself with a knight of Innoruk named Dalion. I dont find that the Tier'dal are evil , though others may find otherwise. They are just being true to themselves. Their actions are questionable, true. Alas I cant condemn my sister Jaranna's actions, as she is being true to herself. So I pull myself out of my chair and find my way to the noises in the guild hall. I then hug my sister Jaranna, and I say &quot;Congratulations dear sister. May your happiness be forever. However watch yourself as well.&quot;<br><br>Jelineth<br>Blindside tellings make the best stories. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=20371A><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bcircleofsisters.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=viviennelileath>Vivienne Lileath</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#660000>(8/28/02 4:37:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fcircleofsistersfrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=267.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.shaw.ca/baddog117/vivieyes.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: *smile*</span><hr size=1> The door to halls suddenly blow open, the wind scattering leaves across the floor. Whispering voices filter in, carried on the cold breeze. A dark, womanly shape stands in the threshold, silhouetted in the lamplight behind her.<br><br>When she steps forward, her bearing is dignified, elegant, with only enough sway in her hips to be attractive, but not overdone. She clothes herself in a dark silk gown that hugs her upper body, and flows down, away from her hips, and as she walks, her heeled boots click quietly on the floor. Her face is down-turned, eyes hidden behind her raven-hair. Spectral visions can be seen surrounding her, half-formed and transparent, images of elven children and women, all clinging to her as though she was their mother.<br><br>“My, my,” she whispers, her voice sounding more hollow, echoing, than it used to, her eyes still downcast, “all this fuss over Jaranna’s desire to be with little me. I am... flattered.”<br><br>Slowly, she lift hers face, and the change is startling. Gone are the crisp, clear blue eyes she once had, replaced by a deep, penetrating blood red. The fires of rage and hatred are clearly displayed behind Vivienne’s eyes. Less immediately visible is the arrogant sneer that now rests on her painted lips, replacing the playful smirk she also once had.<br><br>Vivienne steps up beside Jaranna, sliding her arm around her fiancee’s slim waist. She casts her strange eyes around the chamber, glancing in turn at the frowning faces of each sister and brother, but seeming not to care about their anger and disapproval. Only upon reaching Lady Llylewen does her travelling gaze stop for a moment, and a subtle sadistic gleam comes to her expression.<br><br>With a slight glaring nod of her head at the koada’dal paladin, her eyes turn to meet Jaranna’s. “Vendui, my dear, I trust all is well here? I was just passing by and I heard your voice,” she whispers in a casual tone, “judging by the storm Kelthalas left trailing behind him on his way out, I assumed you must have told these lovely dears about our engagement.”<br><br>Vivienne pauses momentarily, then, with a sadistic smirk and side-long glance at Wardenn sitting quietly, her tongue darts out to moisten her lips. “Perhaps to celebrate this happy news, we should have Wardenn over for dinner?”<br><br><br> <p>Blackest of the black, darker than night<BR>Come to me my bleeding light, see she comes<BR>She comes now, enter oblivion<BR><BR>Here she is, harder than life<BR>In my arms, see she here<BR>Entwined with love, unclean she is<BR><BR>And she comes down to me, and she offers me sleep<BR>Under her black wings<BR><BR><BR>Ilharess Vivienne Lileath<BR>High Mistress of the Sisters of Myth</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bcircleofsisters.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=viviennelileath>Vivienne Lileath</A> at: 8/28/02 4:47:47 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=20371A><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/umirabor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mirabor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elder</span><br>  Posts: 238<br> <font color=#660000>(8/28/02 5:03:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fcircleofsistersfrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=267.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.datazap.net/free/feylin/images/shamanfeather.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: *smile*</span><hr size=1> Delicious smells come from the kitchen. Mirabor has been in there most of the afternoon, hard at work with several new cookbooks and a stack of various meats and bottles of cream. Intent on her cooking, she did not hear Jaranna's announcement such was her focus on a new recipe.<br><br>Hearing the bang of the front door, Mira smiles. &quot;Krys must be home,&quot; she says to herself. &quot;Well, I guess I'll let everyone know it's time fer supper.&quot;<br><br>Grabbing the large heavy iron dinner bell from its small shelf by the kitchen door, she begins to ring it, calling out &quot;Suppertime!&quot; <br><br>Not hearing the immediate stampede of feet which normally accompanies her call, she pokes her head out of the kitchen door. <br><br>&quot;Oh! Vivienne! Vendui. Hello everyone. Erm... supper's ready. . . . .&quot; her voice trails off as the peal of the bell slowly fades into silence. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=20371A><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bcircleofsisters.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kuue>Kuue</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#660000>(8/28/02 5:08:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fcircleofsistersfrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=267.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: *smile*</span><hr size=1> ** the door bursts open in a fury, the wind aiding in its swing.  Rushing through it, a small figure blurred by its quick movement enters the room.  As it slows, Kuue's figure appears, still moving quickly toward the back of the guildhall**<br><br>&quot;Hey everyone!!  Move out of the way...need ta use the little drui...... **stops in his tracks....peering around the room with a look of confusion on his face**  <br><br>**whispers to Bakanome**<br><br>&quot;uh.....Baka....what is a drow doin in the hall, and umm...why are your eyebrows touching each other?&quot;<br><br><br>**after a short pause, realizing he cannot break Bakanomes concentration, he continues on to the back of the hall**<br> <p>Kuue Soulslinger34th circle Druid of TunareClan of Brothers"Bloom where you are planted"</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bcircleofsisters.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kuue>Kuue</A> at: 8/28/02 9:04:31 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=20371A><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ullylewen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Llylewen</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elder</span><br>  Posts: 313<br> <font color=#660000>(8/28/02 5:47:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fcircleofsistersfrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=267.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: *smile*</span><hr size=1> Llylewen stared at Jaranna as the others spoke to her, congratulating her and warning her.  Her face remained emotionless, but she paled slightly and the tips of her ears turned pink.  <br><br>When Vivienne entered and said her her bit, Llylewen just watched.  As the dark elf finished, Llylewen slowly got up and walked over to her, drawing her sword and standing before her.  She glared deep into Vivienne's eyes and lifted the sword and thrust it downward, imbedding it deep into the wood floor.  Turning her glare to Jaranna, she spoke softly and calmly.  &quot;I wash my hands of this.&quot;  Llylewen stripped off her gauntlets and dropped them at Jaranna's feet, then turned and walked out. <p><p><font face="Calisto MT"><img border="0" src="http://www.hyperjump.net/lunap2000/llylewen2.jpg" align="left" width="104" height="104"></font><font face="Invitation" size="4">LlylewenWolfpaw<br>High Elf Paladin of Tunare<br>33rd Season</font></p><p><font face="Invitation" size="4">"...speak softly and carry a bigsword..."</font></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=20371A><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bcircleofsisters.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dalnin>Dalnin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elder<br>Paddle Mistress</span><br>  Posts: 506<br> <font color=#660000>(8/28/02 8:08:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fcircleofsistersfrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=267.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   *nod*</span><hr size=1> Dalnin turns and smiles at Vivienne, noting her complexion, and stature.<br><br>&quot;Your Debt to me is paid, and I wish you well, Don't incure anothere one with my sister. &quot;<br><br>With that  she crosses the room, flicking away her weaponry. THe two enemies stand  face to faceee, and Dalnin hugs the  Teir'dal.<br><br>&quot; Please my sister &quot; she then steps away.<br><br>Something bothers Vivienee though as  Dalnin was close she  smelt different , familiar. hauntingly so.<br><br>She looked down at Dalnin's robe and see her  hair  from  her  no so long ago dead body  is  woven into the monk's  cloak.<br><br>They lock eyes, and the monk  curtsie to her in the fashion of the court of Neriak <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=20371A><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ubakanome.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bakanome</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 49<br> <font color=#660000>(8/29/02 6:51:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fcircleofsistersfrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=267.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: *nod* ( Bear in mind, this was before his change back )</span><hr size=1> Baka stood up, almost entirely ignoring Kuue.  Walking across the room, he stood in front of Vivienne, his Reaver absently hanging from his back.  He unsheathed it and swung all five feet of it slowly towards Vivienne, holding it's tip slowly above her stomach.  A fire burnt within his darkened eyes as he locked them with Vivienne's.  &quot;Vivienne, I've sensed a change in you recently.  As I have changed, so have you.  So I tell you this now, while my conscience is clear.  Hurt Jaranna, or hurt any of my Sisters, or hurt anyone I care about, and I will tear you apart.&quot;<br><br>With that, he turned and walked slowly out of the Hall, his Reaver still in his hand. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=20371A><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bcircleofsisters.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=viviennelileath>Vivienne Lileath</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#660000>(8/29/02 4:28:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fcircleofsistersfrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=267.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.shaw.ca/baddog117/vivieyes.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: *nod* ( Bear in mind, this was before his change back )</span><hr size=1> Vivienne sneers, her lip curling up hatefully at Bakanome. She opens her mouth to utter some rude curse, but a Jaranna grabs her hand that is resting on her hip and gives a quick squeeze. Vivienne looks at Jaranna sharply, annoyed, but her snarl lessens when she meets her fiancee's eyes.<br><br>Vivienne whispers to Jaranna softly, her voice remaining an echoing whisper, &quot;never forget, my dear, I take control from the ones I love, all others, well.... I am now truly my mother's little girl...&quot;<br><br>An utterly cold smile comes to Vivienne's lips as she turns back to the assembled host and nods her head, the sneer never leaving her lips, &quot;I have intruded upon this happy occasion, I am sure you must all be pleased with your sister's decision to marry.&quot;<br><br>Vivienne gives Jaranna a quick kiss before moving back towards the doorway, slowly. Once at the threshold, she stops, turning her head to look over her shoulder at her fiancee, &quot;I shall await you at the manor, my dear? Try not to be too long...&quot;<br><br><br> <p>Blackest of the black, darker than night, come to me my bleeding light<BR>See she comes, she comes now, enter oblivion<BR>Here she is, harder than life, in my arms<BR>See she here, entwined with love, unclean she is<BR>And she comes down to me, and she offers me sleep, under her black wings<BR><BR>Ilharess Vivienne Lileath, High Mistress of the Sisters of Myth</p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fcircleofsistersfrm25.showMessageRange?topicID=267.topic&start=21&stop=21>2</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub101.ezboard.com/fcircleofsistersfrm25.showPrevMessage?topicID=267.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub101.ezboard.com/fcircleofsistersfrm25.showNextMessage?topicID=267.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fcircleofsistersfrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=267.topic&index=20><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/traditional/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fcircleofsistersfrm25.emailToFriend?topicID=267.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fcircleofsistersfrm25.threadControl?topicID=267.topic><img src=http://www.soulcadre.com/Image10.jpg border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fcircleofsistersfrm25.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=267.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fcircleofsistersfrm25.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=267.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receivin